article.description: Tay Waller scored 22 points to lead Auburn to an 89-80 win over Mississippi State on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Waller scores 22 points as Auburn storms past Mississippi St.
article.linkText: Auburn upsets Mississippi St. in coliseum's finale
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. -- Tay Waller scored 22 points and Brendon Knox had 21 to lead Auburn to an 89-80 win over Mississippi State on Wednesday night. The Tigers (15-15, 6-9 Southeastern Conference) had a triumphant farewell in the final game at 42-year-old Beard-Eaves-Memorial Coliseum before moving across the street to Auburn Arena. Waller stayed hot, making 6 of 11 3-pointers and collecting seven rebounds. He has averaged 26 points and made 27 3s over the past four games and Auburn has won three of them. The Bulldogs (21-9, 9-6), who have already clinched a share of the SEC West title, cut a 10-point deficit in half over the final 3 minutes. But the 3s finally stopped falling after Dee Bost scored all 25 of his points in the second half. Bost also had eight assists and went 5-of-9 from beyond the arc.
